    "body": "> I want to see better models on the costs to run a normal validator machine -- say ~5-10 validator instances. Without understanding the fixed costs of a normal consumer setup, discussions of appropriate interest rate are very difficult.\r\n\r\nAt present the simplest approximation is bandwidth, and for that we have fairly clear numbers: 16 KB per 6 seconds per shard, so minimum 2.67 KB/s, maximum 2.67 KB/s * 1024 shards = 2.67 MB/s.",
