    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> I want to see better models on the costs to run a normal validator machine -- say ~5-10 validator instances. Without understanding the fixed costs of a normal consumer setup, discussions of appropriate interest rate are very difficult.\r\n\r\nTrue - also any(?) 'labour' cost of operation needs factoring in.... (Opportunity cost and risk should be factored in too I guess.)\r\n\r\nAnd I'm assuming you're talking about costs for the setup and running of beacon nodes and not just validator clients - referring to: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/issues/157\r\n\r\nEDIT: I don't think bandwidth on its own offers much as an indicator of total costs - unless it's v. high of course (and I'd guess only the top tier nodes could require high bandwidth). Connection latency due to contention ratios and network infrastructure should be more crucial...",
